      <h1>Skincare, decoded for Malaysian skin.</h1>
      <div class="article-body">
        <p>TheBeautyGPT answers one question well: <em>what actually works for my skin?</em> Most of what you find online is either vague or hard to act on. We give clear, evidence-led answers — built for Malaysian skin, weather, and what you can actually buy here.</p>

        <h2>How we work</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Mechanism first.</strong> We explain <em>why</em> something works (or doesn't) before we get to products — hydrocolloid vs microneedle, actives, formulation.</li>
          <li><strong>Real comparisons.</strong> We weigh the actual options you can buy in Malaysia, side by side.</li>
          <li><strong>Local reality.</strong> Prices in ringgit, where to buy (Shopee, Watsons, Guardian), and what suits a hot, humid climate.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Not medical advice</h2>
        <p>Our content is educational. For persistent, painful, or severe skin concerns, see a doctor or a certified dermatologist.</p>
